As a workarounnd you can use
```js
export let diffLevel = 0;

export function diff() {
  if (!(diffLevel -= 1)) {
    console.log("hey");
  }
}

diff();
```
---

If anyone wants to work on this issue, the problem is that `UpdateExpresion`s are always replaced with `+=`: https://github.com/babel/babel/blob/ae0df86340086f2c9e7081921c93b41d1452ddfe/packages/babel-helper-simple-access/src/index.js#L33

It should be used `+=` or `-=` based on `path.node.operator`, like in https://github.com/babel/babel/blob/ae0df86340086f2c9e7081921c93b41d1452ddfe/packages/babel-helper-simple-access/src/index.js#L39
